cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with methods for computing sentence representations, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also explores the performance of different methods for sentence classification, which is a common task in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper uses pre-trained word embeddings, which are commonly used in deep learning models, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The paper also discusses the evaluation protocol for sentence classification, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
